WEBVTT

00:02.073 --> 00:04.074
- So about John...
- You gonna take him on the weekends?

00:04.108 --> 00:06.376
This is something that you
and Ricky need to work out on your own.

00:06.410 --> 00:09.612
Ricky's not gonna get John.
If you don't give Ricky what
he wants, he'll go to court.

00:09.646 --> 00:12.114
Have you ever seen my bedroom?
[chuckles]

00:12.148 --> 00:16.264
We wanna get to know John,
and we wanna make sure
he gets to know us.

00:16.299 --> 00:19.386
Probably the best thing
is for you to get
a mediation.

00:19.421 --> 00:21.407
I might wanna
have real sex

00:21.441 --> 00:23.386
after Betty
and Leo's wedding.

00:23.420 --> 00:25.693
Are we thinking
about having sex?
We are.

00:25.728 --> 00:27.047
Are you excited
about the wedding?

00:27.098 --> 00:28.548
Of course. You're gonna
be there, right?

00:28.582 --> 00:31.045
After all you've done for me,
I wouldn't miss it for anything.

00:31.079 --> 00:33.651
I don't wanna
be friends with you.
Not just friends.

00:33.685 --> 00:35.571
I'm wrong,
and he's right.

00:35.606 --> 00:37.727
Ricky should be able
to take John on the weekends.

00:37.761 --> 00:38.804
Very good decision.

00:38.838 --> 00:40.182
That was the right thing
to do.

00:40.216 --> 00:42.381
And now I don't get to have John
on his first birthday.

00:42.415 --> 00:43.292
You'll work it out.

00:43.326 --> 00:45.279
You and I can plan
the party together.

00:45.313 --> 00:47.430
You can get birth control pills
at the free clinic,

00:47.464 --> 00:49.882
but I suggest
you ask your mother.

00:49.916 --> 00:54.726
You have to be on the pill
at least a month before
they really get started.

00:54.760 --> 00:57.209
I hope that's why I'm late.

01:01.006 --> 01:03.187
[phone ringing]

01:05.810 --> 01:08.596
<i>Hi. What do you need?
[Ricky]
I don't need anything.</i>

01:08.631 --> 01:11.277
I just thought we should talk
about John's birthday party.

01:11.311 --> 01:13.157
[scoffs]
How much do we need
to talk about it?

01:13.191 --> 01:16.582
It's just your family
and my family at the park
tomorrow afternoon around 5,

01:16.616 --> 01:18.728
and then after the party,
you take him home.

01:18.762 --> 01:21.106
<i>Mom's making a birthday cake,
and you're doing
everything else.</i>

01:21.140 --> 01:22.478
Okay. Like what?

01:22.517 --> 01:24.389
Like bringing food
for everyone.

01:24.423 --> 01:25.867
What kind of food?

01:25.901 --> 01:27.372
Just get some wings.

01:27.407 --> 01:29.416
Chicken wings?
Do you want beer with that?

01:29.450 --> 01:31.393
What?
Wings?

01:31.427 --> 01:33.908
I love wings.
Don't you know I love wings?

01:33.942 --> 01:36.452
No. And I the think
the question is,
does John love wings?

01:36.486 --> 01:39.300
<i>It's his birthday.
Wouldn't he choke?
Fine.</i>

01:39.334 --> 01:41.410
Uh, nuggets. I have to go.

01:41.444 --> 01:42.952
<i>I'm trying to be nice here</i>

01:42.987 --> 01:44.458
and include you
in planning the party.

01:44.492 --> 01:45.767
Why are you rushing
off the phone?

01:45.801 --> 01:47.876
Because I have to
get John to bed.

01:47.910 --> 01:49.114
He's not in bed yet?

01:49.148 --> 01:50.619
No. Do you have
a problem with that?

01:50.656 --> 01:52.628
No, I don't.
But his birthday
is tomorrow,

01:52.666 --> 01:54.403
so I hope he gets
plenty of sleep.

01:54.437 --> 01:56.012
I just want everything
to be right.

01:56.046 --> 01:58.691
I never had a birthday party
until I lived
with my foster parents.

01:59.930 --> 02:01.903
I don't know a lot
about this stuff.

02:01.938 --> 02:03.542
<i>It doesn't have to be
anything fancy.</i>

02:03.576 --> 02:06.554
It's not as much for him
as it is for us and our parents.

02:06.588 --> 02:09.666
Celebrating his first birthday
and getting through
this first year together.

02:09.703 --> 02:11.307
<i>He won't even remember it,</i>

02:11.341 --> 02:13.281
but we will, so...

02:13.315 --> 02:14.685
I don't know.

02:14.723 --> 02:16.929
Bring some sandwiches
from the deli.

02:16.964 --> 02:18.770
<i>Some chips,
maybe some balloons.</i>

02:18.804 --> 02:21.110
Yeah, get some balloons.
He loves balloons.

02:21.144 --> 02:23.483
<i>Yeah. And we'll just
hang out for a bit,
and that's it.</i>

02:23.517 --> 02:26.226
After the park,
you'll take him home and have
your first weekend together.

02:26.261 --> 02:29.137
Not a big deal.
Taking him the first weekend
isn't a big deal?

02:29.171 --> 02:32.213
His birthday.
John's first birthday
is not a big deal?

02:32.247 --> 02:35.223
Well, it's a big deal,
but it's not that big of a deal.

02:35.257 --> 02:36.995
I'm surprised
you feel that way.

02:37.030 --> 02:39.068
And I'm happy
you feel that way, Amy.

02:39.102 --> 02:41.240
I'm glad I called you.
I feel a lot better.

02:41.274 --> 02:43.479
The pressure's off.
Thanks.

02:43.514 --> 02:45.921
You're welcome.
See you tomorrow at the park.

02:45.955 --> 02:47.524
All right, Amy.
Good night.

02:47.559 --> 02:49.330
<i>Good night.</i>

02:49.364 --> 02:51.269
Good night.

02:51.303 --> 02:52.505
John.

02:52.540 --> 02:53.978
[phone clatters]

02:54.012 --> 02:55.648
[sighs]

02:57.455 --> 02:59.360
It's just me and you, kid.

02:59.394 --> 03:01.032
Me and you.

03:01.066 --> 03:03.171
All right. So what
no one knows is this:

03:03.206 --> 03:08.086
You and I are gonna have
your birthday party
right now.

03:08.121 --> 03:10.726
It was a year ago
that you started making
your way here,

03:10.760 --> 03:13.033
so I figured,
why not?

03:13.067 --> 03:16.174
And any time that Daddy
has you on a birthday

03:16.208 --> 03:19.181
or a holiday,
we'll have our party
the night before.

03:19.216 --> 03:22.858
You wanna do that?
All right.

03:24.830 --> 03:27.099
I know. Okay, we're gonna
blow it out. Ready?

03:27.133 --> 03:29.034
One, two, three.

03:30.370 --> 03:33.141
Whoa. Yay.
[clapping]

03:33.176 --> 03:34.410
Okay. Ready?

03:34.445 --> 03:35.412
[camera shutter clicks]

03:35.446 --> 03:37.148
[laughs]

03:37.183 --> 03:39.153
Okay, you wanna open
your present, huh?

03:39.188 --> 03:42.427
You wanna open
your present from Mama?

03:42.462 --> 03:45.201
All right.

03:45.235 --> 03:47.539
[shutter clicking]

03:53.854 --> 03:56.393
<i>"Falling in love,</i>

03:56.428 --> 03:59.601
<i>"Is such an easy thing to do.</i>

03:59.635 --> 04:02.174
<i>"Birds can do it,
We can do it,</i>

04:02.208 --> 04:04.646
<i>"Let's stop talking
Let's get to it,</i>

04:04.680 --> 04:07.080
<i>"Let's fall in love."</i>

04:14.315 --> 04:16.048
Amy.

04:18.781 --> 04:20.814
Hey, I just saw John
in the nursery.

04:20.848 --> 04:22.646
Why does he have on a suit?

04:22.680 --> 04:24.544
It's his birthday.

04:24.578 --> 04:26.944
We got up early
and then fell asleep.

04:26.978 --> 04:28.378
Are you gonna have him
dressed up all day?

04:28.412 --> 04:29.478
Why not?

04:29.513 --> 04:31.246
What was on his face?

04:31.281 --> 04:33.348
Are you okay?

04:33.382 --> 04:35.483
You look funny.

04:35.518 --> 04:38.920
It's Mimsy.
Her nurse ju called.

04:38.954 --> 04:41.221
They think she might've
suffered a small stroke
last night.

04:41.256 --> 04:43.223
I have to go up there, Amy.
I don't know if I'm

04:43.257 --> 04:45.624
gonna be able to get back
this afternoon, but I'll try.

04:45.659 --> 04:49.294
Wait. Try, Mom?
It's John's first birthday.
I know, Amy. I know.

04:49.328 --> 04:51.228
Wait. What was on his face?

04:51.263 --> 04:52.830
Uh, breakfast.

04:52.864 --> 04:56.299
Really? 'Cause it looked
more like cake...with frosting.

04:56.333 --> 04:58.033
Okay, you got me.

04:58.067 --> 04:59.901
It was a cupcake.
I gave him a cupcake.

04:59.935 --> 05:02.369
[scoffs]
Amy, did you wake up
this morning,

05:02.404 --> 05:05.672
and have a birthday party
with John all by yourself,
just the two of you?

05:05.706 --> 05:09.374
No. Not exactly.
What if we did?

05:09.408 --> 05:11.075
Well, then, I guess
the rest of us

05:11.109 --> 05:13.743
who went through his first year
with you missed it.

05:13.778 --> 05:17.145
But if that's what you wanted--
you're his mother,
so I guess that's how it is.

05:17.180 --> 05:19.814
Well, that's not what I wanted.
You know what I wanted.

05:19.848 --> 05:21.682
I wanted him to be here
with me this weekend

05:21.716 --> 05:23.684
when it was his birthday.

05:23.718 --> 05:26.919
I didn't know you were gonna
miss the real party--
the one at the park.

05:26.953 --> 05:30.221
Mimsy had a stroke, Amy.
At least they think
that she did.

05:30.256 --> 05:32.656
I have to go to her.
She's in the hospital.
She's my mother.

05:32.691 --> 05:35.024
Well, if she's in the hospital,
she's being taken care of.

05:35.059 --> 05:37.426
You can't wait until tomorrow?
No, I can't.

05:37.460 --> 05:40.762
If you wanted me at the party,
then maybe you could've included
me in the one you just had.

05:40.796 --> 05:43.163
I just said I didn't know
you were leaving,

05:43.197 --> 05:45.798
otherwise maybe I would've.
"Maybe," huh, Amy?

05:45.832 --> 05:48.666
What happened to the girl
last week who stood up
and did the right thing?

05:48.701 --> 05:50.201
Where is she?
I wouldn't have stood up

05:50.235 --> 05:52.836
if I had known that Ricky
would get John for his birthday.

05:52.870 --> 05:54.370
This is completely unfair.

05:54.404 --> 05:57.205
Well, life's not always fair,
Amy, but I guess you know that.

05:57.239 --> 06:00.073
I have to go.
I have to.

06:00.108 --> 06:03.776
Wait. I hope Mimsy's okay.

06:04.877 --> 06:06.711
I really do.

06:06.746 --> 06:08.613
Thanks.

06:08.647 --> 06:12.116
Okay, I'm just gonna go put
a few things in the bag
in case we have to stay.

06:12.150 --> 06:14.284
Wait, wait.
"We" as in you
and Robbie, right?

06:14.318 --> 06:16.518
Dad's not going up there
with you, is he?

06:16.553 --> 06:18.753
Mom, I don't wanna go
to the party with just Ashley.

06:18.788 --> 06:20.922
Amy, you know how much
Mimsy loves your dad.

06:20.956 --> 06:23.957
Yeah. And I know how much
Dad loves his grandson.

06:23.992 --> 06:25.625
I thought I did.

06:25.660 --> 06:27.493
Mom, it's John's
first birthday.

06:27.528 --> 06:29.094
I know, Amy. I know.

06:29.129 --> 06:32.164
It's lousy timing,
but I can't help it.
I can't.

06:32.198 --> 06:34.366
Can't Dad stay up there
and let you come home?

06:34.400 --> 06:35.834
Amy, she's my mother!

06:35.868 --> 06:37.168
Yeah, I know,
but I'm your daughter.

06:37.202 --> 06:39.237
Look, this is difficult
enough as it is, Amy.

06:39.271 --> 06:40.371
Don't make it harder.

06:40.406 --> 06:42.574
[scoffs]

06:44.309 --> 06:45.810
Hey, kiddo.
Your mom got a call.

06:45.844 --> 06:47.778
The nurse thinks Mimsy
might've had a stroke.

06:47.813 --> 06:49.480
We don't know for sure,
so we gotta drive up there.

06:49.514 --> 06:51.182
We may have to miss
John's birthday party.

06:51.216 --> 06:53.550
It's probably nothing.
So I don't have to
go to school?

06:53.585 --> 06:56.586
Not "we" as the entire family,
just "we" as in your mother
and me.

06:56.620 --> 06:58.620
Oh, isn't the divorce
part of the family?

06:58.654 --> 07:01.488
Not my doing.
Yeah, I know.

07:01.522 --> 07:04.857
Uh, look, do you mind
if I go on the pill?

07:04.891 --> 07:06.558
What pill?
What are you talking about?

07:06.592 --> 07:08.226
You know,
birth control pills.

07:08.260 --> 07:10.161
For what?
Skin problems?

07:10.195 --> 07:12.630
You have beautiful skin.
You don't need
birth control pills.

07:12.664 --> 07:14.832
Dear God in heaven,
I'll kill him.
Kill who?

07:14.866 --> 07:17.034
You tell me.
I'm assuming Grant.
It's not his idea.

07:17.068 --> 07:19.869
I just thought this
being the anniversary
of the baby event,

07:19.904 --> 07:21.104
that I'm reminded
of how important it is

07:21.138 --> 07:23.038
to use birth control
if you're gonna have sex.

07:24.674 --> 07:27.547
Please, don't have sex.

07:27.581 --> 07:29.518
You won't like it.
It's not fun.

07:29.552 --> 07:32.054
Dad--
It's not.
Just take my word for it.

07:32.089 --> 07:36.293
All right.
Just so I'm clear,
have you had sex?

07:36.327 --> 07:37.861
No.
Oh, good.

07:37.895 --> 07:40.129
So this is still
under discussion, right?
Right.

07:40.164 --> 07:42.264
You're too young.
Just because you and Grant

07:42.299 --> 07:44.433
have all the working parts
doesn't mean the parts
should be working together.

07:44.467 --> 07:47.135
They shouldn't.
It's fine if they work alone,
but not together.

07:47.169 --> 07:50.004
I really like Grant. I do.
He's a great guy.

07:50.039 --> 07:52.006
But you don't want to have
a baby with him, do you?

07:52.041 --> 07:54.275
No. That's why I'm asking
for birth control.

07:54.309 --> 07:57.210
Yeah, but any time you have sex,
even if you're using birth
control, things can go wrong.

07:57.245 --> 07:59.480
And besides, that's what
sex is for-- making babies.

07:59.514 --> 08:01.347
Yeah, for making babies
and having fun.

08:01.381 --> 08:03.148
No, no, no. I told you,
it's not fun.

08:03.183 --> 08:05.216
Not for you.
Not for the girl.

08:05.251 --> 08:06.818
Come on, Dad.
That's not true.

08:06.852 --> 08:08.320
All right.

08:08.355 --> 08:10.389
But there are a lot of ways
to have fun without having sex.

08:10.423 --> 08:13.426
Yeah, I know. It's just,
like, Grant and I have
been making out a lot,

08:13.460 --> 08:16.030
and I'm really enjoying
making out with him,

08:16.064 --> 08:20.103
and at some point,
we might wanna do more
than that.

08:20.138 --> 08:23.277
But I just wanna make sure
I don't make any mistakes.

08:23.311 --> 08:24.679
You're not gonna make
any mistakes.

08:24.713 --> 08:26.948
Well, I'm sure everyone
who makes a mistake thinks that.

08:26.983 --> 08:29.017
All right.
Years from now,
when you're 18,

08:29.052 --> 08:30.952
then you can have sex,

08:30.986 --> 08:32.953
if it's with the right person
and for the right reason,

08:32.988 --> 08:35.490
and I'll totally sanction you
using the pill as well as

08:35.524 --> 08:37.924
any and all other forms
of birth control.

08:37.958 --> 08:41.394
But, Ashley, please,
please, please wait
until you're out of high school.

08:41.429 --> 08:44.630
I turn 18 before
I get out of high school.
Okay, so we'll compromise.

08:44.665 --> 08:47.133
It doesn't have to be after
you get out of high school,
but wait until you're 18,

08:47.167 --> 08:50.202
and then I promise
I won't fight you on this,

08:50.236 --> 08:52.337
if the aforementioned
circumstances exist
at that time.

08:52.371 --> 08:55.073
All right.
I'll agree to that.

08:55.107 --> 08:58.542
But I wanna be on the pill
anyway just in case.
No. There is no "just in case."

08:58.577 --> 09:01.177
Make sure there's no
"just in case."
Don't let things go that far.

09:01.212 --> 09:03.246
Well, I don't think I would
let things go that far.

09:03.280 --> 09:06.448
But I'm sure lots of people
don't think things will go
that far, and then they do.

09:06.483 --> 09:08.517
What people?
Oh, don't make me say it.

09:08.551 --> 09:11.252
Me and your mother?
Me and Cindy? Me and Kathleen?
Who you talking about?

09:11.287 --> 09:13.254
Kathleen?
Well, no, not Kathleen.

09:13.288 --> 09:15.389
We were actually married first.
And you should be married
first, too.

09:15.424 --> 09:17.157
But I'll go with 18.

09:17.192 --> 09:20.093
What happened, Ashley?
I mean, what prompted all this?

09:20.127 --> 09:22.328
Did you and Grant do something?
I swear I won't be upset
with you.

09:22.363 --> 09:25.664
I just want you
to tell me the truth.
I am telling you the truth.

09:25.699 --> 09:27.800
We haven't done anything,
and I don't think we will.

09:29.001 --> 09:31.736
Dad,

09:31.770 --> 09:34.238
I can see how it can happen,

09:34.273 --> 09:37.107
how even
the most experienced girl
can get pregnant.

09:37.141 --> 09:40.110
What are you talking about?
Amy wasn't the most experienced.

09:40.144 --> 09:41.944
Adrian-- She's the most
experienced, and...

09:46.215 --> 09:49.184
The first thing you should do
is tell your mother.

09:49.218 --> 09:50.852
On her wedding day?

09:50.886 --> 09:52.786
They're getting married today
at some judge's chambers.

09:52.821 --> 09:54.321
I have to go there
after school.

09:54.355 --> 09:56.489
Well, that'll be nice.
No, it's not.

09:56.524 --> 09:58.224
Not for me.
I'm not getting married.

09:58.259 --> 10:01.227
I'm just...having a baby.

10:01.262 --> 10:04.797
You think you're having a baby.
You don't know for sure
if you're having a baby.

10:04.832 --> 10:08.133
You're just late.
You can be late for
all types of reasons.

10:08.168 --> 10:09.735
Stress...

10:11.237 --> 10:12.970
Stress...

10:13.004 --> 10:14.938
Stress or...

10:14.973 --> 10:18.108
Just get an early pregnancy test
and find out, okay?

10:18.142 --> 10:21.611
I don't think you're pregnant,
but if you are pregnant,

10:21.646 --> 10:24.848
then you need to find out
as soon as possible
and let Ricky know.

10:24.882 --> 10:26.949
Ricky?
Yeah. Ricky, right?

10:28.251 --> 10:29.216
Adrian?

10:29.251 --> 10:30.784
Not Ricky.

10:30.819 --> 10:31.885
Not Ben?

10:33.153 --> 10:34.888
No. No, Adrian, not Ben.

10:34.922 --> 10:37.991
Okay. The stupid condom broke,
and I'm on a new pill, and...

10:38.026 --> 10:39.960
And there's a chance
it could still be Ricky's?

10:39.994 --> 10:41.227
No.

10:41.261 --> 10:43.629
It could still be Ricky's

10:43.664 --> 10:47.097
if you say it's Ricky's
and not Ben's.

10:47.132 --> 10:48.131
What?

10:48.166 --> 10:50.466
Who do you wanna marry,
Ricky or Ben?

10:50.500 --> 10:52.467
I don't wanna marry anyone.

10:52.502 --> 10:54.836
I'm not having a baby
if I'm having a baby.

10:54.870 --> 10:57.505
Adrian, you know how
I feel about abortion.

10:57.539 --> 10:59.673
But you're okay with lying
about who the father is?

10:59.708 --> 11:01.241
I'm just trying
to protect Ben.

11:01.276 --> 11:02.709
Oh.

11:02.744 --> 11:05.044
And if you are pregnant
with Ben's baby,

11:05.079 --> 11:07.747
then please don't tell him
this weekend.

11:07.781 --> 11:10.282
His father's getting married,
and he's so happy right now.

11:10.316 --> 11:12.683
Okay, can we just
think about me here?

11:12.718 --> 11:15.853
I'm the one who'd be
having the abortion,
not happy Ben.

11:15.887 --> 11:17.487
No, no, no, Adrian.
That's not an option.

11:17.522 --> 11:20.557
I mean, you didn't get raped
by some criminal
or your father.

11:20.591 --> 11:23.193
You had consensual sex
with a guy you like,

11:23.227 --> 11:24.661
a guy you're friends with.

11:24.695 --> 11:27.263
You have to step up
and take responsibility here.

11:27.297 --> 11:29.932
I am taking responsibility here.

11:29.966 --> 11:32.600
Look, I'm gonna have to do
what I have to do.

11:32.634 --> 11:34.969
I am not having a baby
and ruining my life

11:35.004 --> 11:36.704
like Amy did.

11:36.739 --> 11:40.173
And besides,
I can't be a mother like Amy is.

11:40.207 --> 11:42.575
There's no way I'm gonna
work at a church nursery

11:42.609 --> 11:44.610
and come home
and take care of a baby

11:44.644 --> 11:46.778
and then get up to go to
my senior year in high school.

11:46.813 --> 11:48.346
That's not gonna happen.

11:48.380 --> 11:50.180
Well, we can talk
about all that later,

11:50.215 --> 11:53.550
and we can talk about
other options like adoption.

11:53.585 --> 11:56.286
